          "author_association": "OWNER",
          "body": "Filed from the pd-book-tools deep code/security review.\n\n    Report: `pd-book-tools/docs/research/2026-05-22-deep-code-security-review.md`\n    Finding: #2\n\n    ## Summary\n\n    Training-set export assumes normalized boxes. Pixel-space boxes are multiplied by image dimensions for detection export, and recognition export unconditionally calls scale().\n\n    ## Impact\n\n    Training data generated from Tesseract or other pixel-space OCR is corrupt or crashes.\n\n    ## Evidence\n\n    - `pd_book_tools/ocr/page.py:3322`\n- `pd_book_tools/geometry/bounding_box.py:118`\n- `pd_book_tools/ocr/page.py:3433`\n\n    ## Acceptance\n\n    - [ ] Branch on bbox.is_normalized.\n- [ ] Scale normalized boxes; pass pixel boxes through after clamping/casting.\n- [ ] Add detection and recognition export tests using is_normalized=False.\n\n    ## Notes\n\n    This issue was filed from a read-only review. Confirm behavior with a focused failing test before implementation where practical.",
          "closed_at": "2026-05-22T16:03:37Z",
